G.L. c. 235, \u00a7 8..proposition:
51. Plaintiff seeks recovery of all damages permitted under Massachusetts law for personal injuries caused by negligence, including but not limited to:

   a. Reasonable and necessary past and future medical expenses;  

   b. Past and future lost wages and/or diminished earning capacity;  

   c. Compensation for physical pain, suffering, and loss of function;  

   d. Compensation for mental anguish, emotional distress, and loss of enjoyment of life;  

   e. Any other consequential or incidental damages flowing from Defendant’s conduct, as may be proven at trial; and  

   f. Statutory prejudgment and post-judgment interest and taxable costs. See G.L. c. 231, § 6B; G.L. c. 235, § 8.
